Decision regarding cloud provider can be splitted into smaller sections:

All 4 providers(GCP, AWS, Azure, CloudFlare) supports extensive free tier.

Azur was ruled out because of long cold start. Azure functions can take up to 5 second to run!
https://mikhail.io/serverless/coldstarts/big3/

AWS & Google
Similar qualities, services & pricing. There is no any obstacles to use those providers.
Biggest difference waswit functions. AWS offers 1M per month free, later $0.20 per 1M. GCP offers 2M for free but later it's $0.40

Google downsides:

- paid CDN
- free functions are only in us-east1, us-central1, and us-west1

I haven't investigated AWS that well as GCP.

CoudFlare offers way less services, but is focus more on common usecases like CDN, Storage, DB, hosting.

Storage(instantly accessible item)
S3 - $0.023 per GB
R2 - $0.015 per GB
Google Storage - $0.020 per GB

CloudFlare offers CDN for free. Workers up to 100k daily for free, 10GB R2 for free.
Additionaly we need to use CDN anyway, so it might be our main direction.
